## **The Consensus View: The Ocean Conveyor Belt Collapse**

Before the impact hypothesis gained traction, the scientific consensus focused on a terrestrial culprit: the&nbsp;**Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation (AMOC) Shutdown Hypothesis**.

The AMOC is the “ocean conveyor belt” that transports warm tropical water to the northern latitudes, keeping Europe and North America temperate. The prevailing theory suggests that a massive flood of fresh meltwater from the retreating Laurentide Ice Sheet was suddenly diverted. Instead of flowing south into the Gulf of Mexico, this meltwater pulse was rerouted through the Mackenzie Valley and directly into the Arctic Ocean.

This massive injection of fresh water would have “braked” the AMOC, shutting off the heat supply to the north and plunging the hemisphere back into the freezer.

